The '''United States Senate election of 1870''' was an election which had the [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican Party]] relinquish six seats in the [[United States Senate]], though still retain an overwhelming majority.

As this election was prior to ratification of the [[Seventeenth Amendment to the United States Constitution|seventeenth amendment]], Senators were chosen by [[State legislature (United States)|State legislatures]].

That election marked the first time that, with Mississippian [[Hiram Rhodes Revels]], an African American had been appointed senator (and congressman).<ref>[http://www.senate.gov/artandhistory/history/common/briefing/Facts_Figures.htm  ''official website of the U.S. Senate'']</ref>

==Results==
Senate Party Division, [[42nd United States Congress|42nd Congress]] (1871â1873)

* Majority Party: Republican (56)
* Minority Party: Democratic (17)
* Other Parties: Liberal Republican (1)
* '''Total Seats: 74'''

